FeedPackage.Description:
NLog.Targets.WebSocketServer is a NLog target that instead of writing on a file, or showing the log on the console, broadcast the log entries to the connected websocket connections.
Features:
- Fully integrated with NLog: it does not require changes in your application code beyond the configuration.
- Self-hosted: it does not need IIS or any hosting framework, WebSocketListener is socket based.
- Mono compatible: Both NLog and WebSocketListener are compatible with Mono.
- Subscribe to Regular Expressions: Is it possible to send a message throug the WebSocket connection to indicate the expression to which you want to subscribe. Only log entries matching that regex will be sent.
- Scalable: NLog and WebSocketListener components are decoupled by a producer-consumer pattern, so NLog will append the log entries to WebSocketServerTarget in O(1) time always, and another thread/threads are responsible of distributing that log entry to the clients. Still, if the component has a big number of connected clients, it may interfere with your application performance. See the MaxConnectedClients configuration setting.
FeedPackage.Summary: Broadcast your servers´ logs to websocket connections in real-time with minimal effort. Subscribe to a regular expressions to remove undesired lines.
FeedPackage.Title: NLog.Contrib.Targets.WebSocketServer

FeedPackage.Description:
Azure table storage target implementation for NLog. A fork of harouny's project in github.
The following features set this library apart:
- It supports customizing partition and row keys with macros. For example, you can specify ${longdate}_${guid} in the target "RowKey" property to have your key be made up of a long date/time string and a guid, with an underscore in between.
- It defers the initialization of the azure storage connection till it is actually needed, thus avoiding any startup errors because you have not initialized your connection string yet.
- It detects connection string changes and re-initializes the azure storage connection accordingly. This is roughly modeled after NLog's own DatabaseTarget implementation.
For more information see the project page at https://github.com/abkonsta/NLog.Extensions.AzureTableStorage">
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
Miscellaneous improvements:
- detect and re-initialize connection string if it is changed from code - trace statements to help troubleshoot configuration issues - bug fixes - new macros
FeedPackage.Summary: Azure table storage target implementation for NLog which allows to use macros such as ${date}, ${time}, ${ticks} and many others for partition and row keys. Target initialization is deferred so the logging destination can be changed dynamically.
FeedPackage.Title: NLog.Extensions.AzureTableStorage

- PickupDirectory - NTLM auth
